Cinderella, alone by the fire, dreaming. Andante -
Her Fairy Godmother calls her softly and she gradually wakes -
Cinderella dresses for the ball. Agitato - Cinderella gets into the carriage - She drives away. Allegro - Cinderella has misgivings as tothe result of her adventure - She feels reassured -
Cinderella arrives at the Palace - She watches the dancers. Valse allegro - The ugly sisters attempt to dance - Broadly - The Prince sees Cinderella - He asks Cincderella to dance with him -
The Prince and Cinderella dance together. Tempo di Valse lento - Più mosso - Animato - The Fairy Godmother warns Cinderella - Vivace (roughly) -
The Clock strikes Twelve Heavy - Cinderella runs away, leaving one little glass slipper behind her. Presto -
Cinderella, once more sitting by the fireside, dreaming of the Ball and her dance with the Prince. Andante -
She fances she hears her Fairy Godmother calling her again -
The Prince's Trumpeters are heard in the distance. Tempo di Marcia allegro - The Prince and his attendants set out to search for the owner of the glass slipper. A tempo (very rhythmic) - Più mosso -

The Prince and his attendants arrive at Cinderella's house. A tempo di Marcia - Cinderella's sisters try on the slipper. Più mosso - Allargando - Moderato (broadly) - The Prince tries the slipper on Cinderella's foot -
The slipper fits - Largamente - Allegro molto - Accelerando molto al fine
